data.value: This windows forms app creates JSON files that store information about colours. Pressing one of these two buttons will create and display a JSON file on the left, and then use that file to populate the list view on the right. > Pressing button #1 will create the JSON file using an array of objects written into this program (program.cs). This JSON file is then saved as 'colours1.txt'. > Pressing button #2 will read a pre-written JSON file. This JSON file is called 'colours2.txt'. Both buttons may only be pressed once, to avoid duplicate values in the list view.
